git clone -b Django_Backend "https://github.com/adandotmosta/CinemaTicketBooking.git"
Create a Virtual Environment:
Inside the cloned project directory, create a virtual environment and activate it:

python -m venv my_env
source my_env/bin/activate  # On Linux or macOS
# Or
my_env\Scripts\activate  # On Windows
Install Dependencies:
****Install the project dependencies using pip:

pip install -r requirements.txt
Ensure that you have a requirements.txt file that lists all the required Python packages.

****Database Setup:

python manage.py migrate

***Run the Server:
Start the Django development server:
python manage.py runserver
